$ LibreOffice Writer

{ Keyboard Shortcut Keys

  *F5* toggles the Navigator and corresponds to the menu → development/Software/LibreOffice/Writer/GUI/menu/View/Navigator[View -> Navigator]

}
{ Assigning keyboard shortcuts to styles

  Tools -> customize

  Below ~Functions~, *Category*, find ~Styles~ (last item in list box). Open. Choose Character, Paragraph, Frame, Pages or Numbering.
  
  Styles are then found under *Function*. Choose style, click into *Shortcut Keys* box, select shortcut key.

}
{ (Un-) Docking Windows

  Either
    • `ctrl`-Mouse Click on grey area in window to be docked
    • `ctrl+shift+F10`

}
{ Removing check boxes

  In order to remove check boxes, the document needs to be in *Design Mode*: Menu Edit -> Design Mode.

}

sa:
  → development/Software/LibreOffice
